  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the best massage oil blend for massage quality, feel, popularity among therapists, and skin? (example Grapeseed 75%, Apricot 15%, Jojoba 10%)",
  "response": "Creating the perfect massage oil blend depends on balancing **massage quality, feel, popularity among therapists, and skin benefits**. Here\u2019s a well-rounded blend that meets these criteria:\n\n### **Recommended Massage Oil Blend:**\n- **Grapeseed Oil: 60%**  \n  Grapeseed oil is lightweight, non-greasy, and glides smoothly, making it a favorite for therapists. It\u2019s rich in linoleic acid, which is great for the skin, and has a neutral scent, making it versatile for blending.\n\n- **Sweet Almond Oil: 25%**  \n  Sweet almond oil is highly popular among therapists due to its silky texture and excellent absorption. It\u2019s rich in vitamins E and A, which nourish and moisturize the skin, making it ideal for most skin types.\n\n- **Jojoba Oil: 10%**  \n  Jojoba oil is chemically similar to the skin\u2019s natural sebum, making it highly compatible with all skin types. It\u2019s moisturizing, doesn\u2019t clog pores, and adds a luxurious, non-greasy feel to the blend.\n\n- **Apricot Kernel Oil: 5%**  \n  Apricot kernel oil is lightweight, vitamin-rich, and has a smooth glide. It\u2019s particularly beneficial for sensitive or dry skin, adding a touch of softness and hydration to the blend.\n\n### **Why This Blend Works:**\n- **Massage Quality:** Grapeseed and sweet almond oils provide excellent glide and absorption, allowing for smooth, uninterrupted strokes.\n- **Feel:** Jojoba and apricot kernel oils add a silky, luxurious texture that feels great on the skin without leaving a greasy residue.\n- **Popularity Among Therapists:** This blend combines some of the most widely used and trusted oils in the massage therapy industry.\n- **Skin Benefits:** Rich in vitamins, antioxidants, and fatty acids, this blend nourishes, hydrates, and soothes the skin.\n\n### **Optional Additions:**\n- **Essential Oils (1-2%):** Add a few drops of essential oils like lavender, eucalyptus, or frankincense for aromatherapy benefits and enhanced relaxation.\n- **Vitamin E Oil (1%):** Acts as a natural preservative and boosts the blend\u2019s skin-nourishing properties.\n\nThis blend is versatile, works well for most massage techniques, and is suitable for a variety of skin types. It\u2019s a professional and client-friendly choice!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
